<br>
Go take the whompa from Athen to Broken Shores, you can find the BS whompa to the SW of the other Whompas. After exiting the whompa, turn left and you will find mission terminals a bit down the road. The missions there will mainly go to Varmint woods, Aegen and Avalon. <br>
<br>
Now, if you are below lvl 60 I would recommend to go for Aegen all the way, should give you plenty of cash and is quite fast and easy to get to. <br>
<br>
If you are post 60, choose Avalon. The problem with Avalon is all the red critters and no map. At 60 though, your run speed should be high enough so that none of the critters can catch up with you. <br>
<br>
Some people are taking missions in Tir to Broken Shores, this is supposed to be the most cash awarding route available for clan members due to the long distance between the areas. The problem is that if Avalon is a nasty place, Broken Shores is worse. If I go to Avalon (being post 60) I am fairly certain that I will survive the trip to/from the mission area, in BS I am not, even if it is more rewarding.<br>
<br>
my 2 credits, add comments or other tips if you like. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/urelampago.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Relampago</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://ploskina.com/eqscreens/penguin.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tiny Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 26<br> <font color=#660000>(8/17/01 1:58:10 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Maxing the cash for your missions (clan)</span><hr size=1> How bad is the pk zoning into BS?  I heard people camp the entrance all the time.  I've been doing Avalon and taking missions to Newland rhino camp at 2700 e/w coordinate.  Pays about 11k per at lvl 30.  I&quot;ll give your idea a try tho.<br>
<br>
Sleeg, 30 Clan MA <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#99CC66><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/uylandask.showPublicProfile?language=EN>YlandaSK</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://dynamic.gamespy.com/~cazic/cazic/ubb/profiles/Icon11.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Ninja Wanna-Be</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#660000>(8/17/01 3:50:15 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.home.net/marncrs/pics/ylanda4 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Maxing the cash for your missions (clan)</span><hr size=1> By the Whompa I have never seen any omni, too heavily guarded I guess. The grid entrance is different, I think it goes straight into the OT part of the zone but I have never tried it so I dunno for sure. <p><img src=http://members.home.net/marncrs/pics/ylanda>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/ucwell.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cwell</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Ninja Wanna-Be</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#660000>(8/17/01 4:15:08 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Maxing the cash for your missions (clan)</span><hr size=1> I found that is was faster to do Tyr to Greater Tyr County missions. It is as much dangerous and rewarding, but it seems the run is a little shorter. At 29 i took 3 for 11+k each, then at 30 2 for 11+.<br>
But now at 31, the 12k+ sent me in Varmint Woods, which si preaty close for that much cash <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Kasnohazet. <p><A HREF="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=32876"> Cwell Vaëlmir - Hairy Feet High Priest</A></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#99CC66><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/uhurtyouao.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hurtyou AO</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tiny Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 44<br> <font color=#660000>(8/17/01 6:32:25 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Maxing the cash for your missions (clan)</span><hr size=1> Cwell I agree, on 20-30 greater Tir rocks. <br>
<br>
I may have been a bit unclear in my first post. I should have stated that this was a tip for 40+ players. After a while you will notice that the greater Tir missions will stop showing up when you gain level. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/ukezzic.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kezzic</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Training Dummy</span><br>  Posts: 66<br> <font color=#660000>(8/17/01 7:51:18 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Maxing the cash for your missions (clan)</span><hr size=1> At first I did the Avalon to Tir County and Greater Tir County missions.  Then I started getting missions in Broken Shores (via the whompa in Old Athen).  The problem here, though, is that you will occasionally run into the red mob or the omni camper.  Only saw a camper twice (right by the whompa exit), but it was enough.  The thing with them camping the exit is, unless they take you out right away, you have a good chance of zoning back.<br>
<br>
Then I upped my Comp Lit to 230, and with the +20 generic buff was able to take the grid to Broken Shores.  Note that while there appear to be two Broken Shores exits on the grid, it's the one on the second level you want.  The third level exit requires something like 450 skill and will take you to Avalon.  The grid exit in Broken Shores is in the City of Home.  I'm not quite sure which faction &quot;owns&quot; it, but as a Clan member I am only attacked by a few mobs (none of the humanoids aggro on me).  Now I do missions from West Athen to Broken Shores (West Athen because the grid is right there).  It pays a considerable amount (45k-60k) compared to many of the other missions I see.  I've never seen anyone PvP in the City of Home, but it should be possible.  There seems to be some unspoken truce going on. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#99CC66><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/uvehementi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vehementi</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Ninja Wanna-Be</span><br>  Posts: 22<br> <font color=#660000>(8/17/01 9:25:30 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ...</span><hr size=1> Avalon -&gt; Broken shores = best raw amount of money per mission for clanners. (80k at lvl 71)<br>
West Athen -&gt; Broken shores = also really good (67k at lvl 71)<br>
<br>
Conclusion:  If you are a wee one, I don't care what you do.  Level up.  If you are mid level, grid (251 req) from west athen to broken shores.  If you are big or have a big merit board, grid between Avalon and BS for the best missions.<br>
<br>
-V <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/bthepunchingbag74708.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=alianna>Alianna</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Training Dummy</span><br>  Posts: 97<br> <font color=#660000>(8/22/01 4:55:08 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Maxing the cash for your missions (clan)</span><hr size=1> Or you can try what I do... not as huge a moneymaker but it works for me.<br>
<br>
1. Use the insurance terminal in a place you know will save your position as well as state. Mine is War Academy, but I used to use Freedom. Newland saves position as well.<br>
<br>
2. Go to Avalon and pull missions in a zone that's near your reclaim spot. It helps if you pick a zone that has a lot of mission locations. For me, this is Athen Shire Exp/Wailing Wastes.<br>
<br>
3. Get three missions close together. The Jawa Village is good for this (500x500 in ASE), as are any of the outposts out there.<br>
<br>
4. Terminate. :) Relax for a couple of minutes, get dinner, whatever.<br>
<br>
5. Do all three missions, dump the loot in War Academy, *don't forget to insure when you go in*, run through West Athen and Old Athen and pick up supplies if needed, hit Avalon, rinse, repeat.<br>
<br>
In my 20s, I can usually pull down 30-40k in profit every three missions, and if I do it right, it'll only take me an hour. Oh, the xp is nice, too. :)<br>
<br>
Not the best method, I know, but a decent alternate. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#99CC66><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/urelampago.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Relampago</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://ploskina.com/eqscreens/penguin.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tiny Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 40<br> <font color=#660000>(8/27/01 10:46:25 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Maxing the cash for your missions (clan)</span><hr size=1> Cwell, try taking missions in Tir near the grid access.  Take them for 2600 e/w coordinate in Newland.  I just grid to Newland to cut some time and head out to the rhinocamp in the big crater area.  Not a darn thing touches me while running there and at level 32 I get about 14-15k for reward. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/utrilawhirlwind.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Trila Whirlwind</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Ninja Wanna-Be</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#660000>(9/2/01 2:27:01 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Maxing the cash for your missions (clan)</span><hr size=1> I am level 50 now and I still cannot get Broken Shore missions from Avalon or Tir.<br>
<br>
